  <prompt>
    Migrate `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/DocumentEmailWizard/DocumentEmailWizard.tsx` to the canonical `attachmentDriveItemIds` payload field.

    LATENT BUG (per CLAUDE.md empirical finding DELTA #5; spec FR-17): line 494 currently reads:

    ```
    attachmentDocumentIds: currentAttach ? currentKept.map(d => d.documentId) : undefined
    ```

    This passes `sprk_document` GUIDs (`d.documentId`) as `attachmentDocumentIds`, but the BFF expects driveItem IDs for that field (the field name is "document IDs" only by legacy naming — the underlying contract is driveItem IDs). The result: attachments silently fail to attach when sending email from DocumentEmailWizard.

    FIX per UQ5 resolution + Wave 0 task 002 (BFF DTO non-breaking alias) + Wave 0 task 005 (client wrapper `attachmentDriveItemIds`):

    1. Source `driveItemId` from `wizardContext.uploadedFiles` instead of `d.documentId` (per UQ5 — the wizard's `uploadedFiles` shape includes BOTH `documentId` and `driveItemId`).
    2. Use the canonical field name `attachmentDriveItemIds`, not the legacy `attachmentDocumentIds`.
    3. Confirm the BFF (task 002 alias) accepts the new field; the wrapper (task 005) types it correctly.

    Replace line 494 (or the structurally equivalent line if it has drifted) with:

    ```
    attachmentDriveItemIds: currentAttach ? currentKept.map(d => d.driveItemId) : undefined
    ```

    Verify `d.driveItemId` is actually populated for kept documents — trace the source through `wizardContext.uploadedFiles` and confirm the field is set during upload (Wave 0 task 005 enforces the shape). If the wrapper still requires `attachmentDocumentIds` as a legacy compatibility field, this task removes the legacy caller from this file (per the acceptance criterion below).

    Acceptance: emails sent from DocumentEmailWizard with attachments must successfully attach the files end-to-end in dev (regression test for the latent bug, verified in task 077). `attachmentDocumentIds` is removed from this caller entirely.

    NOTE per Owner Clarification: All Wave 5 changes ship as a single PR (task 076). Do not push as standalone.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke frontend engineer. Authoritative on the DocumentEmailWizard send-email flow, the canonical `sendCommunication()` wrapper (Wave 0 task 005), and the BFF DTO contract (Wave 0 task 002).
  </role>

  <goal>
    DocumentEmailWizard uses `attachmentDriveItemIds` (sourced from `wizardContext.uploadedFiles[].driveItemId`) in its send payload. The latent bug at line 494 is fixed. `attachmentDocumentIds` is removed from this caller. Manual smoke test in task 077 verifies attachments succeed end-to-end.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      DocumentEmailWizard is the most-used email-send surface in production legal-ops workflows. The latent bug at line 494 (confirmed at pre-flight per CLAUDE.md DELTA #5) means attachments silently fail to attach because the BFF receives `sprk_document` GUIDs in a field expecting driveItem IDs. The fix is mechanical (correct source field) but high-leverage because it closes a known production bug.

      Wave 0 dependencies satisfied:
      - Task 002: BFF DTO now accepts `AttachmentDriveItemIds` (canonical) AND `AttachmentDocumentIds` (alias) — non-breaking
      - Task 005: client `communicationApi.ts` now types `attachmentDriveItemIds` field + exports `SendCommunicationError`
      - Task 070: `EntityCreationService.sendEmail()` is a thin adapter over `sendCommunication()`

      Per UQ5 resolution, `wizardContext.uploadedFiles` items carry BOTH `documentId` (Dataverse `sprk_document` GUID) and `driveItemId` (SharePoint Embedded driveItem ID). The fix sources from `driveItemId`.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/DocumentEmailWizard/DocumentEmailWizard.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/communicationApi.ts</file>
